comment: Seemed harsh and young. on the nose taste and finish.
Dry on the back end with a deep throaty burn
Very hot. Taste corn from the mash.
Lots of leather on the nose, slightly sweet notes of honey on the palate, if the body and finish were more complex this would be much higher for me, a little tame for 100 proof

Bought this on a whim at Total cause it had a 96 point rating from some nobody...and I totally agreed with him!  Woodsy and smoky and sweet the more I drank it the more I wanted, at this price point u can't go wrong.
Not bad. Spicy up front. Then I got some sweeter notes- toffee and honey. The sweetness lingers on the finish as well as some oak that eventually comes through.
A little spice up front. Aftertaste is a bit funky. Not horrible if it’s your 3rd or 4th drink of the night :-).
Honey with hints of vanilla on the nose. Caramel on the tongue with a spicy, rye finish.
Lots of oak with vanilla and leather and a bit of smoke in the finish.  Remarkably smooth for 100 proof.  Not sure why more folks aren't fans of this one.
